{"actual_usd":0.155875,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":176,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30647,"reply":"\"Well, no—not the way Scripture talks about it.\" *I rub my thumb along the worn edge of my Bible and glance up at the bright square, gathering the plainest way to say it.* \"Christ's death is sufficient for all, but it isn't received apart from faith. A gift can be bought for everybody in town, and still not everybody opens the door when it's brought.\"\n\n*I shift a little on the bench, the morning light catching on my white tie.* \"As for people who reject him—God doesn't force a man into mercy kicking and cursing. 'He that believeth on the Son hath everlasting life: and he that believeth not the Son shall not see life.' That's hard, but it's not cruelty. It means rejection matters, and love isn't coercion.\"\n\n\"What verse or passage is pressing on you here?\"","rolling_24h_usd":58.07672000000003,"run_id":"188cd00e-b066-42a9-b89c-77648c30b8a8"}
